modules.description: This module generates random values in various numeric formats, including 8-bit, 16-bit, 32-bit, and 64-bit integers, as well as arbitrary and bounded integers and floats. It accepts a function that produces random byte strings as input and uses it to derive these numeric values. Concrete use cases include generating random integers for cryptographic nonces, test data, or simulation inputs, and producing random floating-point numbers for statistical sampling or randomized algorithms.
